A plan to build a new football stadium in Carson, CA came one step closer to reality this week after the Los Angeles registrar certified that the measure had the signatures needed to qualify for a spot on the ballot.&nbsp;
Carson city council members will meet on Tuesday to decide whether to approve the ballot initiative for a public vote or bypass the process altogether and adopt the plan outright.&nbsp;
